{
  "name": "Crowd Control",
  "type": "feat",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You are experienced with influencing crowds. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Diplomacy on checks against crowds. The first time each round you Stride into a square containing a crowd, you can attempt a @Check[type:diplomacy|dc:20] check to try to move the crowd out of your way. A GM may use a different DC under certain circumstances, such as when the crowd has a level or set DC to disperse.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> As success, and the crowd departs from all adjacent squares as you move.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The crowd disperses from squares you move into.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The crowd doesn't move, but you can continue moving.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The crowd forcefully resists you and disrupts your Stride.</p>"
    },
